														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3681562">
									

<p>My main issue with this article is that it feels contrarian for the purpose of being contrarian. There's no real larger point to it all except &quot;normal is abnormal&quot; - which, while correct in this context, doesn't do anything for me.</p>
<p>My secondary problem is that the prose feels off in a way that I can't really pinpoint. A good chunk of it is definitely due to the shortness of the article - there isn't enough time for me to really get invested in this proposal or whoever it is that's proposing it. However, at the same time, it also feels overstretched - the core idea is too simple to elaborate on without repeating yourself and using fluff (the abstract section highlights this issue well; you're placing too much emphasis on stuff that the reader would be able to infer even if the bench <em>was</em> anomalous in some way).</p>

							</div>

