			<div class="content" id="post-content-3682311">
									

<blockquote>
<p>now my question is should I keep this article up for context or let the readers know just by the tale?</p>
</blockquote>
<p>In general I advise against self-deleting. If it comes down by standard process, well that's just how she goes sometimes; and this discussion thread might pick up more useful feedback you can use in the time it takes for that to happen.</p>
<p>In the process of writing the tale you might find yourself revising the details of the art installation that the story revolves around, and end up with a rewritten version of this GOI-Format that will stand solidly as it's own seperate article. Or you may simply fold the entire idea into one piece. It'll just take the time and effort of trying different things and getting feedback on what works or what doesn't.</p>
<p>For the record, I've decided to give an upvote here for the thought-provoking concept. Though I reckon I might like it better if the article itself did a bit more of the legwork on exploring that concept. Good luck with your follow-up efforts!</p>

							</div>

								
					
